nt is then\nscored according to the Agatston scale.\n-This scoring system provides risk stratification to help predict the likelihood of a\ncoronary accident occurring within the next five years\nTracing the vessels\n-determined using a contrast enhanced coronary CT\n-To evaluate the anatomy, identify congenital anomalies, and detect various\npathologies such as atherosclerosis, stenosis, occlusions, and vasculitis\nCardiac MRI\nCardiac MRI is a comprehensive modality that can assess\nmorphology, function, viability, and valvular pathology in a\nsingle examination.\n• Key Clinical Uses: Detection of Ischemic Heart Disease (IHD)\nand viability, diagnosis and risk stratification of\ncardiomyopathies, and postoperative assessment of congenital\nheart disease (including extra-cardiac shunts).\n• Technical Advantages:\n◦ No ionizing radiation or radioactive materials (as\nthallium).\n◦ Not restricted by the acoustic window issues that affect\nECHO.\n84"}